        <h2 class="section-title">Why Fix My Diaper exists</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">A small project built from a very real parenting problem.</p>

        <div class="text-block">
          <p>
            Becoming a parent completely changed the way I experience the city.
            Before having a baby, I never noticed whether a café had a changing table,
            whether a bathroom could fit a stroller, or whether a place was truly welcoming to families.
          </p>
          <p>
            Suddenly, these details shaped every outing. Fix My Diaper was created to make that information visible:
            a practical map and discovery platform built by parents, for parents.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

